Patch Set 2:

First of all, a small tweak (diff is vs this patch) that I made...  Which I am not 100% sure about, but...

I previously hadn't decided what to use for extension size (the size we check for), but this seems correct - just use the whole component size since it can't change.  The risk is that we would deny a component that would fit if it isn't filled up...  But since this is supposed to be an "intermediate" component, it seems OK to not push for using all the space.  (And "intermediate" components should not be extremely large.  The "use the full size of the component" thing is mostly a concern for *very large* components and/or infinite size components, which will obviously never fit.  But this component is in the middle, so it should be OK.)

"--- a/lustre/lod/lod_object.c
+++ b/lustre/lod/lod_object.c
@@ -6778,8 +6778,11 @@ static int lod_sel_handler(const struct lu_env *env,
                /* extension size uses the stripe size field as KiB */
                extension_size = lod_comp->llc_stripe_size * SEL_UNIT_SIZE;
        } else {
-               // TODO: Tunable or at least named constant
-               extension_size = lod_comp->llc_stripe_size * 10;
+               /* normal PFL components cannot adjust later if the OSTs fill
+                * up, so we use the full component size in that case
+                */
+               extension_size = lod_comp->llc_extent.e_end -
+                               lod_comp->llc_extent.e_start;
        }
"
